[{"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion KoblenzEZ-1010 A - St 32 2EZ-1010EigZulG: GeneralEStG: 10iEigZulG: 2EigZulG: 4EigZulG: 6EigZulG: 7EigZulG: 9 / 2EigZulG: 9 / 3EigZulG: 9/11 / 4EigZulG: 9 / 4EigZulG: 6EigZulG: 9 / 6EigZulG: 6 / 17BdF IV B 3 - EZ-1010 - 11/98 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "10 2 1998 BStBl 1998 I 190 Doubtful questions about the EigZulG and the deduction of preliminary costs for an apartment benefiting from the EigZulG (\u00a7 10i EStG) here: Further information on the introductory letter for the application of the EigZulG and the \u00a7 10i EStG (BMF letter dated 10 2 1998 - IV B 3 - EZ-1010 - 11/98 -) 1 Buildings on third-party land (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "7 10 + 1322 beneficial owner (\u00a7 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "83 Construction of an apartment (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "11 12 + 1324 apartments that are subject to value-in-use taxation (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "18 5 Acquisition by the spouse (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "196 Use for own residential purposes (Section 4 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "25 62 + 1327 Spatial connection (Section 6 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "418 Funding for follow-up property (Section 7 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "529 Basic funding amount in the case of co-ownership (Section 9 (2) EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "64 - 6610 heat recovery systems (Section 9 (3) EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "7711 Additional funding for low-energy houses (Section 9 (4) EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "8212 procedure (Sections 11 - 15 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "93 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "13 Determination for spouses (Section 11 (6) sentences 3 and 4 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "10114 Requirements for the cooperative (Section 17 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "106 + 10715 Personal requirements of the comrade (\u00a7 17 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "108 + 13216 Child allowance for two eligible parents (Section 17 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "114 The following explanations of the individual paragraphs of the introductory letter mentioned in the subject are intended as additional help for legal questions in the case of corresponding cases and represent the current administrative opinion, nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "14 and 15 also include IT changes from 19 3 19981 buildings on third-party land (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "7 10 + 132A beneficial owner can also acquire beneficial ownership of a building he has erected on third-party land, provided certain additional requirements are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The BFH ruled with judgment of 27 November 1996 - X R 92/92 - (DStR 12/97 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "448 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": ") affirmed beneficial ownership in a case in which the sole owner of an undeveloped property had a single-family house built together with her future husband, the construction costs of which were both shared halfway"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the judgment, the two builders had concluded a - also hereditary - contractual user agreement before the start of construction, according to which the non-owner-builder may use the building like a co-owner for its expected useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The civil-law owner was thus not entitled to any claim for compensation until the building was economically consumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The BFH saw this as an actual - economic - restriction of the owner's power of disposal, because in the event of a sale she would be liable to pay compensation to the person entitled to joint use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The owner's right to surrender after the agreed period of use is no longer relevant in these cases, because the building is economically consumed at this point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This BFH ruling is applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If a manufacturer builds an apartment for his own residential purposes on someone else's property with the consent of the owner and is entitled to an inheritable right of use for the estimated useful life of the apartment on the basis of a clear agreement made prior to development, he is also entitled to claim"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, in cases in which a usage agreement is made for the expected useful life of the apartment after its completion, no beneficial ownership is assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the client of an apartment built by him on third-party land subsequently acquires ownership of the property under civil law, he can receive an owner-occupied home allowance for the construction of the apartment from the year in which the notarial contract was concluded, provided that this begins with the completion of the apartment The funding period has not yet expired, d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "On the one hand, only the remaining funding period is favored and, on the other hand, it is now a manufacturing case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the builder inherits the property, he can receive a home ownership allowance from the year of death"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The previous view that the building owner acquired the apartment in the event of the subsequent transfer of the property under civil law in exchange for the reimbursement of expenses is no longer adhered to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The BFH in a further decision of 11 12 1996 - X R 263/93 - (FR 8/97, p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "301 f"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": ") represented opinion, according to which there is no claim for reimbursement of expenses according to \u00a7 951 paragraph 1 sentence 1 BGB, if renovation work is carried out on a property with a view to future property acquisition and then ownership of the property or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "House is transferred to the person who initiated the construction work, corresponds to the decision of the Federal Court of Justice of 12 July 1989 cited by the court (BGH, NJW 1989 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "2745 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In the opinion of the BGH, the decisive factor is that, in the case of construction work on someone else's property, a claim to enrichment derived from Section 812 (1) BGB - regardless of the time of the expenditure - only arises when the failure of the expected later transfer of ownership is finally certain"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Claims for reimbursement of expenses based on the actual realization of the underlying expectation can no longer be asserted if ownership of the property is later transferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the civil law property is only transferred from the parents as owners to their children who initiated the construction years after the construction work has been carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Until the final failure of the purchase expectation based on an agreement (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": ": Refusal to vacate the property), regardless of which legal norm it is based on, the claim for reimbursement of expenses is pending (BGH, NJW 1970 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "136 f"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "As long as the prospective transfer of ownership of the built-up property is still to be expected, the property owner can oppose the intended future transfer of ownership to a claimant for reimbursement of expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "A claim for reimbursement of expenses exists only in cases in which the - final - failure of an expected later transfer of ownership is established"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Only if it is proven that a later transfer of ownership has not been agreed or even excluded can a purchase be made against the abandonment of the claim for reimbursement of expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the construction of buildings on third-party land begins before 1 1 1998, the beneficiary can irrevocably request that the owner-occupied home allowance according to the legal principles of no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "5 17 42 and 48 of the BMF letter of 31 12 1994 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "887), unless he has already received an owner-occupied home allowance or deductions according to \u00a7 10e EStG for this construction project"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "2 Beneficial owner (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "8 The person entitled to permanent residence i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7\u00a7 31 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "WEG is to be regarded as the beneficial owner of an apartment if the permanent right of residence contract corresponds to the model contract for the order of property-like permanent right of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Such a contract model is in Bundesbaublatt 1956 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "615 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "printed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "As requested several times, a copy of this is attached as an attachment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "3 Construction of an apartment (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "11 12 + 132 On the question in which cases an apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 10e Abs 1 EStG is established, the previous administrative view was already in Tnrn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "14 and 15 of the BMF letter of 31 December 1994 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "887)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "According to this, an apartment is produced when the construction work results in an apartment in the legal valuation sense for the first time and the building fabric used is so profoundly redesigned or expanded to such an extent that the inserted parts of the apartment created give the impression and the old parts used appear subordinate in value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, this can be assumed if the construction costs plus the value of your own contribution roughly exceeds the value of the old building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the construction of an apartment does not require the construction of a new building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The BFH judgment of 15 November 1995 - X R 102/95 - (BFH / R 5/96, p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "93 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "in BFH / NV 96) as well as the BFH judgment of 11 September 1996 - X R 46/93 - (BB 4/97, p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "189 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "), on the other hand, the opinion can be inferred that the construction work on an - existing - apartment must be equivalent to a new building in order to obtain an apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 10e Abs 1 EStG to be able to accept"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, the BFH refers to the term \"structurally new\" building i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Case law on degressive depreciation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "According to the administrative opinion, however, the legal opinion already represented on \u00a7 10e EStG on the creation of an apartment is to be transferred to the Eigenheimzulagengesetz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In principle, the construction of an apartment requires the creation of a structurally new apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "However, it is waived in those cases in which the construction measure creates an - additional - apartment in the sense of valuation law for the first time (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "by expanding the attic, by adding or dividing an apartment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "It is still sufficient here that the construction costs incurred in the temporal and material connection with the creation of the apartment plus the value of the personal contribution, according to a rough calculation, exceed the value of the old building substance (market value)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In the comparison calculation between construction costs and old building substance - in accordance with the BFH - typical maintenance expenses are to be excluded if there are no near-acquisition production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "As far as margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "12 sentence 3 - deducting the maintenance effort when the question of whether a new apartment has been built - affects the beneficiaries to the disadvantage, the regulation applies for the first time to apartments, the construction of which begins after December 31, 1997"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The opinion that the purchaser of a renovated condominium can receive the new construction subsidy of up to DM 5000 annually if the renovation expenses attributable to the apartment have exceeded the proportional value of the building substance (see R 43 para 5 EStR 1996), with the proviso that through Such an extensive renovation of an apartment has been made is not followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Even the acquisition of an apartment that has already been refurbished or is still to be refurbished only leads to funding under Section 9 (2) sentence 1 of the EigZulG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "up to DM 5000 if the renovation measures result in an apartment in the sense of valuation law for the first time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "4 apartments that are subject to value-in-use taxation (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "18 Pursuant to Paragraph 2 (1), second sentence, of the EigZulG, the granting of an owner-occupied home allowance for an apartment that is still subject to value-in-use taxation is excluded because of the priority of the deduction of income-related expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Extensions and extensions to such an apartment are to be included in the value in use taxation, as long as the taxpayer does not waive them"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is, however, that the living space is only marginally enlarged through the expansion or expansion (construction measure of minor importance)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If a tax citizen submits an application for a home ownership allowance for such a construction project, which is then finalized, and if he does not waive the application of the value-in-use taxation in his later-submitted income tax return, the final home ownership allowance notification can be changed to Section 175 (1) sentence 1 no 2 AO be supported because the right to home ownership is based on the behavior of the taxpayer or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "the income taxation based on it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "So if he decides to keep the value-in-use taxation when submitting his income tax return, the facts relevant to the allowance will be changed with retroactive tax effect in the past, so that the requirement for the granting of the allowance no longer applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "5 Acquisition by the spouse (Section 2 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "19A new entitlement to a home owner's allowance is not justified if the beneficiary purchases an apartment or a part of it from his spouse and the spouses are subject to unlimited income tax at the time of purchase and do not live permanently apart"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "However, the acquiring spouse can continue to receive the allowance at the previous amount from the year following the year of acquisition until the end of the funding period, as long as the requirements of Section 26 (1) EStG are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the property is transferred for a fee, partially paid or free of charge.This means that in the case of spouses who meet the requirements for a joint assessment, the acquiring spouse can claim the allowance for an apartment acquired by the other spouse during the funding period or can continue a share from the year following the year of acquisition, as would have been granted to his spouse transferring the property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "6 Use for own residential purposes (Section 4 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "25 62 + 132 The home owner's allowance is an annual amount and the beneficiary is entitled to the full amount even if he only uses the apartment for his own residential purposes during part of the year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "However, this does not lead to an allowance for holiday apartments outside a designated holiday area, which are therefore allowed to be inhabited year-round according to building law (no application of Section 2 (1), variant 1 of the EigZulG), and which are only available for a short period of time (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "only 14 days) are self-used and otherwise rented out, especially in the case of holiday apartments lent to a national tour operator, for which a high loss regularly occurs, the criterion \"serve residential purposes\" is not fulfilled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Rather, the regulation of R 42a Paragraph 1 Clause 3 EStR 1996 is to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This applies in particular if the owner generally has the option of using the apartment himself during the periods in which the apartment is not rented out, but makes use of it in different ways over several years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply if the beneficiary started construction of the property before November 1, 1998 or acquired the apartment on the basis of a legally binding contract concluded before this point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "7 Spatial connection (Section 6 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "41\u00a7 6 (1) sentence 2 EigZulG excludes the simultaneous promotion of two spatially connected spouses' property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The BMF letter dated December 31, 1994 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "887, Appendix 34 III EStH 1996) in margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "28 sentence 6 gives the spouses the opportunity to forego further funding of the first property in favor of funding the second property with the consequence of double property consumption if they subsequently purchase or manufacture the second property in the spatial context within the deduction period of the first property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "A corresponding right to choose between two home ownership objects does not exist, because \u00a7 11 EigZulG does not provide for a correction standard for such cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Section 172 (1) sentence 1 no.2 letter a AO also does not apply in the present case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This provision only allows changes to unlawful notices and does not allow legal and final home ownership notices to be changed to the detriment of the beneficiary upon application for the purpose of exercising a right to vote again - and this time differently"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The beneficiary can, however, waive the further funding of a \u00a7 10e property in favor of a home ownership property that is located in a spatial context - but also here with the consequence of double property consumption"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "8 Funding for follow-up property (Section 7 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "52 Spouses who each have four unused years left over from each other and independent first properties from the time before the marriage, cannot combine the funding into a subsequent property with an eight-year funding period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Similar to spouses who first choose a follow-up property subsidy but then opt for the second property subsidy, it is permissible here to switch from the shorter follow-up property subsidy when one property is not used to the longer follow-up property subsidy for the other property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "9 Basic funding amount in the case of co-ownership (Section 9 (2) EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "64 - 66 In the case of a share in a single-family house or a condominium, the beneficiary can only receive the corresponding part of the basic funding amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if, in addition to the beneficiary, a person who is not subject to unlimited income tax is co-owner of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the beneficiary sells a share of co-ownership in an apartment that was previously solely attributable to him, he can receive the basic subsidy amount in full in the year of the sale and the purchaser can receive a proportion of the amount in accordance with his co-ownership share"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the co-owner of a two-family house or multi-family house uses an apartment under \"own legal jurisdiction\", he can receive the basic subsidy amount - as well as deductions according to \u00a7 10e EStG - in full"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the co-owner expands his apartment so that the value of the apartment no longer corresponds to his co-ownership share, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "by adding a subsidized winter garden, he can only receive part of the home ownership allowance for the extension"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The principles of legal jurisdiction also apply if co-ownership was only established subsequently"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "10 heat recovery systems (Section 9 (3) EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "77 Contrary to the interpretation of Section 82a EStDV, the condensation part contained in a condensing boiler does not belong to the favored heat recovery systems from exhaust gas, because this is not a heat recovery system, even if it works like one technically"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The condensation part only leads to a better utilization of the calorific value of the heating system"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "11 Additional funding for low-energy houses (Section 9 (4) EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "82 The information on the heat requirement certificate according to sample A is mathematically incorrectly presented in the FINDEX version of the purchase order"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "I would therefore ask you to consult the paper version of this ruling in cases of doubt"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to the OFD-Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "from 2 6 1997 - EZ-1220 A - St 32 2 -"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "12 procedure (Sections 11 - 15 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "93 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The setting of the home ownership allowance for all years of the funding period is an administrative act - with permanent effect"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "By the JStG 1997, \u00a7 4 of the Small Amount Ordinance has also been changed to the effect that the minor regulations have been extended to the area of \u200b\u200bhome ownership allowances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "It follows from this that the DM 20 limit applies to the entire funding period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "13 Determination for spouses (Section 11 (6) sentences 3 and 4 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "101 Here are u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "two groups of cases are regulated in which the previous stipulations are not to be revoked"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The first variant concerns the marriage of co-owners of an apartment during the funding period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the allowance must be re-determined from the year of marriage in accordance with Section 11 (6) sentence 4 2 Alternative EigZulG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The previous individual determinations are not to be repealed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The second variant concerns the elimination of the requirements of Section 26 (1) EStG in the course of the funding period, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "because the spouses separate, and there the constellation that both spouses can continue to claim the home ownership allowance after the separation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "From the year following the year of separation, the allowance must be set separately for each spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The consolidation is not to be canceled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Both regulations apply with regard to external cancellations - with notification -"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In order to avoid double payments, internal cancellation measures are always necessary in these cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "14 Requirements for the cooperative (Section 17 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "106 + 107Prerequisite for the promotion of the business shares is that the articles of association of the cooperative irrevocably grant the members of the cooperative who receive the promotion, the hereditary right to purchase the property of the apartment used by them for residential purposes in the event that the majority of those in an object Resident cooperative members have given their written consent to the establishment of residential property and the sale of the apartments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "A cooperative that provides members with heritable building rights, only builds community facilities and also builds rental apartments, does not meet these funding requirements, as its activities are not geared towards the production or purchase of cooperative apartments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the articles of association of a cooperative contain a temporary ban on converting the apartments into condominiums, this does not correspond to the requirement of a property-oriented cooperative"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If there is no housing stock when the cooperative is founded, the cooperative's actions must be geared towards the production or purchase of apartments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, the home owner's allowance is to be set provisionally in accordance with Section 165 (1) AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the explanatory text 695 must be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "\"The setting of the home ownership allowance for the purchase of cooperative shares is partly provisional because there has been no housing stock since the cooperative was founded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "\"This change will be included in the DA EDP"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "The technical application takes place on March 20, 1998 for the test calculation on March 19, 199815 Personal requirements of the comrade (\u00a7 17 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "108 + 132 The beneficiary can also receive the home ownership allowance for the years of the funding period in which he does not use a cooperative apartment for his own residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "However, personal use must begin in the last year of the funding period at the latest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply to beneficiaries who joined a cooperative that had already been established before 14 2 1998"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the cooperative is already entered in the cooperative register at this point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "However, if the beneficiary only joined the cooperative after 14 2 1998 (cf. OFD-Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "dated 5 2 1998 - EZ-1170 A - St 32 2) and if he has not previously lived in a cooperative apartment, the notification identification 11 (Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "1110 = 11; \"The decision is partly provisional according to \u00a7 165 Abs 1 AO\", cf. addition of OFD No. 5 of the Reference Ordinance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "dated 4 3 1998) and the explanatory text 696"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "\"The setting of the owner-occupied home allowance for the acquisition of cooperative shares is partly provisional because the cooperative apartment has not yet been used for own residential purposes and joining the cooperative did not take place before February 15, 1998"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Please inform the tax office if this apartment is used for your own residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If the cooperative apartment is not used for personal residential purposes by the end of the funding period, the home ownership allowance paid will be reclaimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "\"These changes are also included in the DA EDP"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "At the time of the technical use of the program, see No. 1416 Child allowance of two eligible parents (Section 17 EigZulG) - margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "114 In the case in which spouses A and B each have a share i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "If you earn 10,000 DM, both spouses can receive the full child allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165284.xml"}, "text": "Income tax / income tax / church taxRhineland-Palatinate Kw / 98/20 // Eigenheimzulagengesetz, preliminary cost deduction, questions of doubt // STED"}]